Proposed direction
Colors. Deep forest green as primary (think pine forest, not mint). Sage/moss as secondary. Warm cream or off-white as background (never pure white — pure white is 2015 SaaS, not nature). Charcoal for text, never pure black. The chain colors are their own thing: mossy dark green, softer sage green, warm ochre (not alarming yellow), dusty terracotta (not aggressive red).
Typography. Editorial serif for headings — something like Fraunces, GT Sectra, or Recoleta. Clean geometric sans for UI and body — Inter or Söhne. This combination is what makes it feel editorial/professional instead of app-y. Headings with serifs feel considered, permanent. Most habit apps use all sans-serif and that's why they read as generic.
Layout. Generous whitespace, wider margins than feel necessary, content breathes. Cards/tiles have subtle borders, not heavy drop shadows. Rounded corners but subtle (8–12px, not 20px+). Texture used minimally — maybe a barely-there paper grain on the background, nothing more.
The home screen visual anchor. Instead of a tree, the chain itself is the hero. A horizontal row of recent weeks, each week a colored tile. Current week at the right, glowing softly, not yet "sealed" until Sunday. Past weeks slightly dimmer. This is the image you want burned into your mind — the chain, unbroken, stretching back.
